As per Matt Q:

{quote}
we should definitelly allow to turn it off -- we get the info without extra processing, but we could save the index-space by ignoring it
{quote}

Currently you cannot turn it off in the UI and the [docs|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/FISHEYE/Store+Diff+Info] mention that you can't for CVS.

diff stars are missing - you cannot star a diff at all. see https://extranet.atlassian.com/crucible/browse/FE/trunk/src/content/WEB-INF/jsp/committer/committer.jsp?r1=37865&r2=37933 

in the breadcrumb star is a file star. Instead it should say 
{quote}
... > path > to > file > filename.ext : _r1234_ : _r2345_ (*)
{quote}
where the (*) is a star for the diff of revision 1234 and 2345, and the revision numbers should be linked.

-----

revision star is missing from the page which it would be most likely starred - the annotated view of a revision. see https://extranet.atlassian.com/crucible/browse/FE/trunk/src/content/WEB-INF/jsp/committer/committer.jsp?r=37933

the breadcrumb of that page should be a revision star:
{quote}
... > path > to > file > filename.ext : _r1234_ (*)
{quote}
where the (*) is a star for the revision 1234, and the revision numbers should be linked.
